programme.title: Great Games: All-Star
programme.desc: The 2008 MLB All-Star Game at Yankee Stadium was marked as the longest All-Star Game in history. It ended after 4 hours and 50 minutes in the 15th inning on a walk-of sacrifice fly from Michael Young.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/7/52: Mickey Mantle's 6th inning home run and Billy Martin's game-saving catch help the New York Yankees win their 4th straight World Series, beating the Brooklyn Dodgers in 7 games.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/14/65: Sandy Koufax finishes a complete-game shutout in Game 7 of the 1965 World Series to bring home a championship. The Dodgers' 2-0 victory was capped in the top of the 4th inning when runs scored on a homer and an RBI single.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/15/70: After allowing three runs in the 1st inning, Mike Cuellar silenced the Reds over the next eight frames to pitch a complete game. The Orioles offense backed his start, scoring nine runs on 15 hits to take Game 5 and win the 1970 World Series.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/22/75: Tony Pérez started the Reds' comeback in Game 7, smashing a two-run home run over the Green Monster and onto Lansdowne Street. Jim Burtan scored Ken Griffey in the top of the 9th to break a 3-3 tie and give the Reds their third World Series win.

programme.title: All-Star Highlights
programme.desc: Check out highlights from the 1967 MLB All-Star Game. The AL and NL were represented by some of baseball's best, including Rod Carew, Carl Yastrzemski, Roberto Clemente, and Hank Aaron.

programme.title: Baseball Seasons
programme.desc: Two of the most unforgettable endings in Postseason history occur in 2003. The Aaron Boone Game takes center stage in the series between the Yankees and Red Sox, while fans of the Marlins and Cubs are left talking about Beckett and Bartman.

programme.title: World Series Films
programme.desc: This World Series Film showcases the 1958 matchup between the Yankees and the Braves. A rematch of the 1957 World Series, Milwaukee took a 3-1 series lead into Game 5 before the Yankees came roaring back to secure their 7th World Series title in 10 years.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/11/1977 - Paul Blair singles home Willie Randolph in the bottom of the 12th inning to give the Yankees a walk-off victory against the Dodgers in Game 1 of the 1977 World Series.
programme.sub-title: Paul Blair walks it off to win Game 1

programme.desc: Are sparrows and blackbirds the direct descendents of a vicious group of dinosaurs including the velociraptor?

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: According to new evidence, the Woolly Mammoth went on roaming until about the time the Pyramids were built.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: How do modern archaeologists extract info from a dig? A dig at an Iron Age hill-fort at Danebury is the focus.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Horizon follows scientists across the world on a quest to solve the riddle of the Hobbit.
programme.sub-title: The Mystery of the Human Hobbit

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Investigating bog-bodies - victims of pre-historic murders whose corpses have remained intact.

programme.title: Walking with Beasts
programme.desc: Special effects-filled documentary beginning 49 million years ago. The world is heavily forested and birds rule the planet, preying on small mammals. Whales have not yet evolved and their ancestors walk on the land.

programme.title: Walking with Beasts
programme.desc: A pregnant basilosaurus, an 18-metre, carnivorous whale which lives in the Tethys Sea, is forced to kill the young of a smaller whale to ensure the survival of her unborn calf.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise
programme.desc: The Caribbean is a tropical paradise. From just a few meters wide, to hundreds of kilometers across, each of the over 7,000 islands are different, and each has its own unique wildlife.
programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island
programme.desc: Lying like a teardrop in the Indian Ocean, Sri Lanka is an island that defies convention. Poised just six degrees above the equator, it's less than 75,000 km sq in size. But it has enough wildlife to rival a continent.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise
programme.desc: The Falkland's bleak, battered, and windswept archipelago lies 460 km from the South American mainland. Rugged mountains and expansive pristine coastline are a unique home for wildlife  especially for one of the world's most iconic flightless birds.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds
programme.desc: The longest chain of mountains in the world, the Andes run the length of western South America and dictate the climate for the whole continent. They include some of the highest peaks outside the Himalayas.
programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado
programme.desc: Venezuela is famous for its lost worlds, its forbidding mountains, huge swamps, and impenetrable jungles, all seemingly cut off in space and time. Yet each is linked, by the mighty river: the Orinoco, the rumoured route to El Dorado, city of gold.
programme.sub-title: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Amazon: One Jungle, Many Worlds
programme.desc: The Amazon is the largest rainforest in the world, and the richest ecosystem on earth. This film uncovers what makes the Amazon such a powerhouse of evolution; how it has come to home a third of all species on the planet.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth
programme.desc: Patagonia is a place of extremes  of vast ice fields and snow-capped mountains; of windswept deserts, and violent oceans. Survival here means being tough enough to cope with brutal winters, and canny enough to exploit brief seasons of plenty.
programme.sub-title: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Pantanal: Brazil's Wild Heart
programme.desc: Every year the Pantanal is drowned by immense floods, and then suffer severe drought. Yet, while people struggle, the Pantanal hosts some of the greatest gatherings of animals on the planet.

programme.title: Wildest India: Western Ghats: Monsoon Mountains
programme.desc: See how the Himalayas run across 2,500km of north India.The Himalayas' highlands offer little direct refuge to humans. /Then, learn about the western Ghats. A spine of mountains that lay claim to being one of the most bio-diverse places in the world.

programme.desc: We meet several individuals who claim they have the ability to transcend time and space and identify people, objects, and locations hidden from their view.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Freemasons
programme.desc: Are the Freemasons a harmless fraternity whose members busy themselves by raising money for children's hospitals or a satanic cult whose tentacles and enslave mankind?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Mokele Mbembe
programme.desc: Mokele Mbembe means able to stem the flow of rivers. The Pygmies there say they have encountered just such a creature and according to their descriptions, this behemoth is a dead ringer for an Apotosaurus.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Bigfoot

programme.desc: Richard investigates a UFO sighting over Chicago's O'Hare airport that was witnessed by dozens of people, including an airline captain, his crew and several airport officials.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Philadelphia Experiment

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Phoenix Lights

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Agenda 21
programme.desc: Is Agenda 21 simply a non-binding, voluntarily implemented action plan of the United Nations with regard to sustainable development?

programme.title: Myth Hunters

programme.sub-title: The Nazis and the Book of Power

programme.title: Myth Hunters

programme.title: Myth Hunters

programme.title: Naked Science: Making Mountains

programme.title: Naked Science: Snowball Earth

programme.title: Naked Science: Anatomy Of A Hurricane
programme.desc: Hurricanes are one of the most destructive weather events to strike our planet and have the same power as a nuclear weapon.

programme.title: Naked Science: Super Flares - Could They Cause Mass Extinction?

programme.sub-title: Super Flares - Could They Cause Mass Extinction?

programme.title: Naked Science: The Great Flood

programme.title: Naked Science: How To Avert an Asteroid Impact

programme.sub-title: How To Avert an Asteroid Impact

programme.title: Naked Science: Venus
programme.desc: Earth has an evil twin. Venus. It is shrouded in a lethal atmosphere of carbon dioxide and acid rain. The surface temperature is hot enough to melt lead and the pressure high enough to crush a nuclear submarine.

programme.title: Naked Science: The Big Bang - The First Three Seconds
programme.desc: 13.7 billion years ago there was absolutely nothing. No space, no time, and no matter. Naked Science follows the first three seconds of creation when a speck of light appeared from nothing and rapidly expanded into an enormous Universe.
programme.sub-title: The Big Bang - The First Three Seconds

programme.title: Naked Science: Magnetic Earth
programme.desc: The Earth hurtles through space protected by an invisible force field, known as a magnetosphere.

programme.title: Naked Science: Atmosphere
programme.desc: We breathe it every day, it protects us from solar radiation, controls our weather – it’s the atmosphere. Naked Science takes a trip from the earth to near space to understand how the earth’s atmosphere affects all life on the planet.

programme.desc: A tornado in Oklahoma traps a family with nowhere to hide. Heavy rains in Tennessee put a construction crew in danger when a hillside crashes down. A flash flood ravages a trailer park, forcing a heroic rescue of mother and two daughters.

programme.title: Full Force Nature

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Extreme Animals
programme.desc: Extreme Animals features environments hostile to humans, but havens to many animals. Witness gorgeous glow-worms, high flying condors, parched thorny devils, emperor penguins, and polar bears in this journey through life on the edge.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Arks
programme.desc: Cut off from continents, remote islands have become floating arks, attracting migrating species and forging new ones. Take a privileged glimpse into the secret lives of the rare and exotic species that inhabit these lost worlds.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Water Adventures
programme.desc: We are captivated by oceans, rivers, and lakes - the power, the flow, the reflective stillness. And as we seek to get closer, we immerse ourselves in an expanding range of aquatic experiences.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanic Islands
programme.desc: They've been worshiped and feared over the millennia. But in the wake of drama and destruction, the elements give rise to cultures and nations so beautiful that we've come to know them as the world's greatest volcanic islands.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Port Cities
programme.desc: Some of the most stunning cities are port cities - Sydney, Rio, Cape Town - and are also some of the most culturally diverse and vibrant. The great maritime cities of the world bridge countries and continents and unite the global community.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Power and Persuasion
programme.desc: This episode explores Hitler's approach to propaganda in power; where persuasion was achieved through propaganda and terror, all in service of one goal: the creation of a state under one shared ideology. A new German power fueled by propaganda.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Why We Fight
programme.desc: This episode explores the way Hitler used propaganda to justify his warmongering, reframing it as defense of Germany’s people and borders. It investigates the role propaganda played for both Hitler and the Allies to mobilize their countries for war.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Tragic Sinking of Leopoldville
programme.desc: On the 24th of December 1944, 2 237 American soldiers of the 66th Infantry Division are aboard the Steamer Léopoldville.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: Secret Bunkers of Omaha Beach
programme.desc: On June 6th 1944, Lieutenant-colonel Rudder’s Rangers company climbs the cliffs of the Pointe du Hoc in Normandy with the mission to destroy the German cannons.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Last Flight of the B-17
programme.desc: Twenty-six metres beneath the waves at the foot of the majestic Calvi Citadel in Corsica lies an American plane from the Second World War.
programme.sub-title: The Last Flight of the B-17

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Lost Tanks of D-Day
programme.desc: In Normandy, June 6, 1944, a dozen Sherman tanks equipped with floats, the famous Duplex Drives (DD), leave their ship to swim to Omaha Beach... not all of them make it.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: A Terrible Precedent
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Arsenal of Democracy
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Unprecedented, Unmerciful and Unrelenting

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: Hitler finds his political destiny in post-war Munich. He quickly dominates a fringe party & builds it into the Nazi Party. He recruits infamous men to the cause including Herman Goering & Heinrich Himmler & they plot a coup known as the Beerhall Putsch.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: In 1924, Hitler is convicted for High Treason after the failed Nazi power grab. In prison, he writes Mein Kampf, articulating his anti-Semitic and expansionist beliefs. Upon release, Hitler rebrands the Nazi Party.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: In 1930s Germany, Hitler capitalizes on economic woes blaming the Weimar Government and Jews. Despite scandals, Nazi rallies gain popularity and emerge as the largest party. Hitler becomes Chancellor in 1933, using the 'Enabling Act' to seize power.

programme.title: The Rise of the Nazi Party
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's secret agenda is to rid Germany of Jews. By 1938, after creating work schemes and rearming, he orchestrates "The Night of Broken Glass," burning 1,000 synagogues and killing 91 Jews, preparing for further aggression.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Democracy without Democrats 1929-1933
programme.desc: Democracy Without Democrats 1929-1933: A protest turns into a racist and anti-Jewish movement during the 1920s and the NSDAP use emotions to gain the loyalty of the people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Racial State 1933-1934
programme.desc: The Racial State 1933-1934: President Hindenburg suspends freedom of speech and Hitler comes to power in 1933. The first concentration camps for political opponents are set up.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Hidden in Plain Sight 1935-1938
programme.desc: Hidden In Plain Sight 1935-1938: In 1934, Hitler's government is firmly in the saddle. Most Germans support Hitler's anti-Jewish policy and the regime's terror soon escalates.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Up in Flames 1936-1940
programme.desc: Up in Flames 1936-1940: At the end of 1939, the German Army invades Poland. Examine how Hitler succeeded in pushing through his rearmament and war plans relatively unhindered.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942
programme.desc: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942: In the shadow of the war, the Nazi regime gradually advances its "final solution to the Jewish problem", culminating in the Holocaust.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Genocide 1942-1944
programme.desc: Genocide 1942 - 1944: Along with Treblinka and Majdanek, Sobibor was one of the camps used in Operation Reinhard, in which the Nazis murdered almost two million people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Armageddon 1943-1945
programme.desc: Armageddon 1943-1945: The defeat at Stalingrad in 1943 was the turning point of the war and convinced the Nazi leadership to intensify their terror and propaganda campaigns.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Reckoning 1945-1948
programme.desc: The Reckoning 1945-1948: In 1945, WWII was over but the violence had not ended. The survivors want to blame the Germans. The reckoning with National Socialism is ambivalent.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Cro Magnon
programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Grand Union Canal

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Leeds & Liverpool Canal
programme.desc: This canal turned Liverpool into the busiest port on Earth.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Moving Bridges
programme.desc: Moving Bridges: Exotic milestones on moveable infrastructure. Historically significant: the Kaiser Wilhelm Bridge and the Michigan Avenue bridge. Mechanically unique: the Pont Jacques, the Gateshead Millennium Bridge or the Scale Lane Bridge.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Railway Bridges
programme.desc: Railway bridges fascinate through different construction methods from masonry, truss-beam bridges to steel-concrete arch bridge. Heavier loads, faster speeds, more frequently: trains speed over bridges and the maintenance teams face ever larger challenges

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Steel Bridges
programme.desc: Steel bridges are extremely durable and multifunctional, fascinating not only due to its gigantic size but also because of the army of workers keeping the bridges in shape: whether on the historical landmark in Sydney or ultramodern mega bridges in China.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Road Bridges
programme.desc: Road bridges: gigantic constructions of modern road traffic. Europa and Ganter Bridge, Öresund bridge, Sunshine Skyway and Viaduct de Millau.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Suspension Bridges
programme.desc: Suspension bridges – impressively wide and stretched high over supporting cables or stay cables. The landscape-shaping icons: The superlative Golden Gate, Akashi Kaikyo, Aizaih, El Baluarte and Russky Bridge.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Power Generator
programme.desc: A three hundred and ninety ton giant on a daring journey: A team of German heavy-lift-specialists have to transport a generator from a disused coal plant to its new operation site 120 kilometers away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: ITER Magnet
programme.desc: This giant magnet will revolutionize the world and energy production in the future. The world's largest nuclear fusion reactor is currently under construction in southern France.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Drilling Rig
programme.desc: A brand-new oil rig, worth 500 million dollar, has to go from South Korea to Europe. The problem is that it is too gigantic for a heavy transport vessel. The solution is to tow it.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Siberian Ice Road
programme.desc: A Mega Transport on one of the most dangerous roads in the world. The Siberian Ice Road. It doesn't forgive mistakes. It's treacherous. And unpredictable.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Giant Antenna
programme.desc: South America. The chelonian Atacama Desert is home to the world's largest radio telescope Atacama Large Millimeter Array Observatory, also known as ALMA.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Mining Truck
programme.desc: If a transporter needs to be transported, if 176 wheels aren't enough to carry its weight and if the load weighs twice as much as the transporter... Then it must be the mother of all mega transports!

programme.title: Mega Transports: Wind Park
programme.desc: A wind park needs to get from Europe to Asia. Over two thousand tons of highly sensitive and valuable cargo. On one of the world's largest heavy lift vessels.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Gigantic Autoliner
programme.desc: A transport to the other side of the globe. The Höegh Trapper is the largest automobile transporter in the world. Two hundred meters long, thirty-six meters wide.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Biggest Containership
programme.desc: When the first ship of the brand-new OOCL-fleet gets underway, more cargo is moved at one time than anywhere else in the world and ever before.

programme.title: Mega Transports: AutoClav
programme.desc: A unique mega transport made of steel and titanium with a special purpose: to extract tons of gold. This so-called autoclave is the biggest of its kind. Its weight: over one thousand tons.

programme.title: Ancient Alien America
programme.desc: Native cultures have handed down shocking accounts for generations of Aliens from other worlds visiting Earth in the ancient past and their involvement with them.

programme.title: Aliens in Egypt
programme.desc: New evidence of highly advanced, precision machining on Egypt's Giza Plateau gives credence to the Ancient Alien hypothesis further supported by glyphs of futuristic vehicles, bizarre flywheels, and other artifacts and monuments cut with laser precision.

programme.title: Dulce Base: The New Illuminati
programme.desc: Dulce, New Mexico is a hotspot for mysterious phenomena and alleged secret military collaboration between humans and aliens.

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: Texas UFO
programme.desc: This episode includes: Scared to Death, Texas UFO, Butch Cassidy and Sibling Search & Update.

programme.title: Alien Contact: Secret Societies
programme.desc: Thousands of years ago a special, genetically advanced race of beings came to Earth. They were seen as Gods by primitive man and worshipped. They set themselves apart.

programme.title: Ancient Alien Origins
programme.desc: Researchers discover that aliens from another world assisted in the evolution of man and were the genesis of a very real bloodline that remains intact today.

programme.title: Alien Paranormal: Bigfoot, UFOs and the Men in Black
programme.desc: Are Bigfoot creatures traveling to earth in UFO's, and being covered-up by Men in Black? Experience terrifying, real events as documented by top authorities, including: Aliens attacking a house; Alien Abductions to create a hybrid race; vortexes and more!

programme.title: UFO Hunters: The Italian Ufologists
programme.desc: Italian researchers explore mass UFO sightings, clipeology, and real testimonies, delving into the history and research methods of ufology.

programme.title: Ancient Aliens : Origin of Humanity
programme.desc: Increasing evidence and sightings of UFOs suggest contact with extraterrestrial beings who may have influenced the origins of human life.

programme.title: Aliens in the USSR
programme.desc: Unsolved Soviet Union Alien Mysteries: Dyatlov Pass incident, Petrozavodsk miracle, Voronezh case. Amaze and frighten, but doubt of alien involvement.

programme.title: Alien Mind Control: The UFO Enigma
programme.desc: This fascinating documentary offers an unprecedented look at a group of individuals who claim to have had life altering UFO encounters, and discovers the unique psychic abilities they unknowingly share.

programme.title: UFO Conspiracies: The Hidden Truth
programme.desc: This documentary charts the US government's involvement with UFO phenomenon from 1947 to the present day. Featuring rare classified footage, expert interviews, cover-ups and the revelation of a secret 20 million dollar UFO research program.

programme.title: Hopkinsville: The Alien Goblins
programme.desc: A family fights off goblin-aliens in a mysterious encounter, sparking debates and investigations. Fear drives their actions.

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: Belgian UFO

programme.title: Proudest Girl In The World, The
programme.desc: A musical recruiting film for the Canadian Women's Army Corp.

programme.title: This Borrowed Land
programme.desc: This Borrowed Land" highlights women farmers in BC's Peace River Valley, protesting hydro dam construction threatening their farmland. They question land use, food production, and their children's future in a film on agriculture, ecology, and resilience.

programme.title: Ill Find A Way
programme.desc: When nine-year-old Nadia is allowed to attend a regular school, she knows the kids will tease her but she'll "find a way to deal with it." Nadia has spina bifida, a congenital condition that has caused a lack of sensation from the knees down.

programme.title: George And Rosemary

programme.title: Minoru Memory Of Exile
programme.desc: The bombing of the American naval base at Pearl Harbor, by a nation he knew only by name, thrust nine-year-old Minoru Fukushima into a world of racism so malevolent he would be forced to leave Canada, the land of his birth.

programme.title: Adams World
programme.desc: Adam's World present a short lecture by Elizabeth Dodson Gray, a feminist theologian, environmentalist, and futurist. She speaks to us about the severity of our global environmental crisis, and analyzes the root cause of this crisis.

programme.title: Voices Across The Water
programme.desc: ‘Voices Across the Water’ follows two master boat builders as they practise their art and find a way back to balance and healing.

programme.title: Doctor Lawyer Indian Chief
programme.desc: A tribute to Indigenous women everywhere, this short documentary focuses on 5 women from across Canada. They talk about the importance of Indigenous culture in helping them to develop a sense of self and seeing through rough times.

programme.title: Undertaker For Life!
programme.desc: Undertakers are anything but gloomy; they’re funny, generous and dedicated. We would gladly go on vacation with them, but sadly, they never have any dead time.

programme.title: Flamenco At 515
programme.desc: This Oscar-winning film is a visual and emotional thriller. It is an impressionistic record of a flamenco dance class given to senior students at the National Ballet School of Canada by two great teachers from Spain, Susana and Antonio Robledo.

programme.title: Maud Lewis A World Without Shadows
programme.desc: Against a backdrop of charming paintings and the Yarmouth, Nova Scotia landscape they reflect, Maud Lewis: A World Without Shadows celebrates the life and work of one of Canada's foremost primitive painters.

programme.title: Mary Two-Axe Earley I Am Indian Again
programme.desc: This film shares the powerful story of Mary Two-Axe Earley, who fought for more than two decades to challenge sex discrimination against First Nations women embedded in Canada’s Indian Act and became a key figure in Canada’s women’s rights movement.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Women At War
programme.desc: This 1942 British film, Women at War, contrasts sharply with similar Canadian productions. It accepts women's direct participation in the war effort as a natural outgrowth of their peacetime occupations.

programme.title: Tu As Crie Let Me Go
programme.desc: In "Tu as crié LET ME GO," Anne Claire Poirier explores her daughter's tragic descent into drugs and prostitution, seeking understanding of the societal pressures influencing young people's risky behaviors in Montreal's streets.

programme.title: The Story Of Peter And The Potter
programme.desc: When Peter accidentally breaks a glass bowl intended as a birthday gift for his mother, Mr. and Mrs. Deichmann and their daughter Anneke, all artisans in clay, come to the rescue and make him one of their designs while Peter watches.

programme.title: Sea Dream
programme.desc: Children, like adults, have days that go wrong. This film shows how one little girl overcomes the day's frustrations by diving into an underwater fantasy where she spends time with her friend, the lady octopus.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Wings On Her Shoulder
programme.desc: This is a 1943 recruitment film. Although it specifically promises women jobs in post-war aviation, its primary message is that women fulfill support positions "so that men might fly.

programme.title: Christophers Movie Matinee
programme.desc: When movie cameras were put in the hands of a few young people, they made this film about themselves and their world. The film is revealing in what it shows of a dissenting generation and its rationale.

programme.desc: Die Stars der Volksmusik begleiten Dagmar Obernosterer vom Defereggental in Osttirol in das Antholzertal nach Südtirol. Gottfried Würcher, die jungen Zillertaler, Sarah-Stephanie, die Alpenrebellen u.v.a. sind dabei, wenn die Apres-Ski-Party beginnt.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten
programme.desc: Eine herrliche Bergkulisse und traumhafter Pistenspaß - die Grubertaler und Marc Pircher bringen eine ordentliche Portion Hüttenzauber in Ihr Wohnzimmer. Hochkarätige Interpreten wie Mara Kayser, Oswald Sattler & Doris Russo sind ebenfalls mit dabei..
programme.sub-title: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten

programme.title: Freddy Quinn LIVE - Lieder, die das Leben schrieb: Teil 1
programme.desc: Er reiste um die Welt, begeisterte ein Millionenpublikum und schaffte es zehn Mal auf Platz 1 der deutschen Charts. Freddy Quinn ist einer der letzten großen Entertainer Deutschlands. 2002 gab der Österreicher ein bewegendes Abschieds-Konzert in Wien.

programme.title: Peter Kraus - Ganz nah
programme.desc: Peter Kraus ist die deutsche Rock'n'Roll-Legende! Wie er privat denkt und fühlt, das zeigt sein Sohn Mike in einem außergewöhnlichen Portrait. Er begleitet seinen Vater auf Tournee und ermöglicht einzigartige Einblicke hinter die Kulissen.

programme.title: Goldies: Folge 1
programme.desc: Auf dem Mond da blühen keine Rosen / Cora komm nach Haus / Marleen / Ganz in Weiß / Du fängst den Wind niemals ein / Es fährt ein Zug nach Nirgendwo / Santa Maria

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Villnösser Tal in Südtirol
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert wieder die Stars der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik - diesmal vor der malerischen Kulisse des Villnösser Tals in Südtirol. Mit dabei sind unter anderem Oswald Sattler, die Zellberg Buam und Anneliese Breitenberger.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast im Villnösser Tal in Südtirol

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer stellt uns ihre Heimat Kärnten vor. Mit dabei sind u.a. die Schäfer, die Alpenrebellen, die Grubertaler, die Zellberg Buam, die Jungen Original Oberkrainer und der Sieger der Vorentscheidung zum Grand Prix der Volksmusik - Udo Wenders.

programme.title: Ein Festival der Liebe: Teil 2
programme.desc: Zu Tausenden strömten gut gelaunte Schlagerfans 2010 in den Dortmunder Revierpark Wischlingen, um ihre Lieblingsstars hautnah zu erleben. Nicole, Chris Roberts, Guildo Horn u.v.a. machten dieses Open Air Konzert zu einem echten "Festival der Liebe".

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Brandnertal
programme.desc: In dieser Ausgabe von "Lieder, Land & Leute" entführt Sängerin und Moderatorin Dagmar Obernosterer die Zuschauer in das wunderschöne Brandnertal. Vor der alpinen Kulisse des Vorarlberg geben Stars aus Schlager und Volsmusik ihre Lieder zum Besten.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Bad Waltersdorf in der Steiermark
programme.desc: Im oststeirischen Hügelland, in der Thermenregion Bad Waltersdorf, begrüßt Sie Dagmar Obernosterer. Die Sendung steht im Zeichen von heißen Quellen und großen Stars. Mit dabei sind u.a. die Stoakogler, die ein Medley ihrer größten Hits präsentieren.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Bad Waltersdorf in der Steiermark

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Berggenuss und Seenspaß
programme.desc: Kärnten hat vielleicht die schönsten Badeseen Österreichs. Viele Sonnentage und Wassertemperaturen bis 28 Grad machen Kärnten zu einem Urlaubsidyll. Musik gibt es von Andreas Gabalier, den jungen Zillertalern, Saso Avsenik und seinen Oberkrainern u.v.a.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Südtirol
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer stellt das Ahrntal und Algund bei Meran vor. Auch ein Ausflug auf Schloss Juval, Wohnsitz des berühmten Südtiroler Bergsteigers Reinhold Messner, darf nicht fehlen. Mit dabei sind Stars wie Oswald Sattler, Mara Kayser, Janine Lenk u.a.

programme.title: Gala der Stars auf hoher See
programme.desc: GoldStar TV sendet von der 'Costa Classica'. Frederic Meisner und Jutta Niedhardt stellen Ihnen das Traumschiff vor. Für musikalische Unterhaltung ist selbstverständlich auch gesorgt. Freuen Sie sich auf Stars wie Roland Kaiser, WIND, André Stade u.v.a

programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: Festividades do Chocolate Quente
programme.desc: Colette dirige uma cafetaria conhecida pelo seu chocolate quente secreto e famoso. Marcus, um novo dono de sobremesa, começa a atrair os clientes da Colette, ela está determinada a expô-lo.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Natal Feliz
programme.desc: Após a morte de seu pai, um menino cria um vínculo especial com o cachorro de um vizinho e aprende a ser um homem ajudando seus avós durante uma tempestade de inverno.

programme.title: José e Maria
programme.desc: Em 30a.C., Herodes reinava sob Israel até que o nascimento do Messias ameaçava a sua soberania. Surge então nessa jornada de fé e milagres uma mulher, Maria e um homem, José, escolhidos por de Deus para cuidar daquele que salvaria a humanidade, Jesus.

programme.title: Um Natal em Canaã
programme.desc: Um fazendeiro viúvo do Texas convida seu novo lar para conhecer a família no Natal, apenas para descobrir que as alegrias da temporada mascaram um anseio muito mais profundo.

programme.title: Um Amor Inesperado
programme.desc: É Natal e Sammi está buscando um pouco de sossego. Viciado em trabalho, Seth vem da cidade grande para explorar um terreno que recebeu de herança e que ele pretende vender antes do final do ano. A tranquilidade de Sammi é interrompida pela chegada de Seth

programme.desc: Crie uma atmosfera calorosa de férias em sua casa com as imagens e sons do Natal, filmados em alta definição.

programme.title: Una aldea navideña
programme.desc: Para salvar su reputación, Piper Jensen, una genio en relaciones públicas y dueña de su propia agencia de relaciones públicas, acepta trabajar para el dueño de un Pueblo de Santa en dificultades, ahí descubrirá el amor y cuán mágica es la navidad.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Otra vez Navidad
programme.desc: Un chico travieso se despierta cada mañana del día de Navidad con la ilusión de tener un regalo, pero nunca lo recibe. La única manera de romper esta maldición es darse cuenta de que es un egoísta y corregir su actitud.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una aldea navideña
programme.desc: Para salvar su reputación, Piper Jensen, una genio en relaciones públicas y dueña de su propia agencia de relaciones públicas, acepta trabajar para el dueño de un Pueblo de Santa en dificultades, ahí descubrirá el amor y cuán mágica es la navidad.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Otra vez Navidad
programme.desc: Un chico travieso se despierta cada mañana del día de Navidad con la ilusión de tener un regalo, pero nunca lo recibe. La única manera de romper esta maldición es darse cuenta de que es un egoísta y corregir su actitud.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una aldea navideña
programme.desc: Para salvar su reputación, Piper Jensen, una genio en relaciones públicas y dueña de su propia agencia de relaciones públicas, acepta trabajar para el dueño de un Pueblo de Santa en dificultades, ahí descubrirá el amor y cuán mágica es la navidad.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Otra vez Navidad
programme.desc: Un chico travieso se despierta cada mañana del día de Navidad con la ilusión de tener un regalo, pero nunca lo recibe. La única manera de romper esta maldición es darse cuenta de que es un egoísta y corregir su actitud.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Einer der symbolträchtigsten Lebensräume der iberischen Halbinsel ist der Mittelmeerwald, das Land des Iberischen Luchses, einer einzigartigen und faszinierenden Raubkatze mit einer Erfolgsgeschichte bei der Erhaltung der Tiere. Korkeichen und Steineichen sind die Herren dieser herrlichen Wälder. Und diese Wälder beherbergen eine einzigartige und endemische Fauna. Damit ist diese Region einer der wichtigsten Biodiversitäts-Hotspots der Erde.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Sich um die eigenen Kinder zu kümmern ist der wunderbarste Job der Welt. Aber es ist auch der schwerste, anstrengendste, komplizierteste und manchmal wirklich aufreibendste. Ab und zu kann man fast nachvollziehen, dass manche Tiere sich gar nicht um ihren Nachwuchs kümmern.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Amazonas
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Invasion der Heuschrecken
programme.desc: Seit Menschengedenken haben Heuschrecken die Prärien und Felder Westafrikas heimgesucht und Zerstörung und Verzweiflung zurückgelassen. Was wissen wir über sie und was verwandelt scheinbar harmlose Insekten in gefürchtete Raubtiere?

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Jordanien
programme.desc: Der Mittlere Osten ist eines der heißesten, trockensten Gebiete der Erde, mit Jordanien in seinem Herzen. Das harte Leben der Tiere wird hier von der Sonne regiert. Jedes Jahr steigen die Temperaturen und die Wüste wächst.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Wieder einmal verwandelt sich das Land. Andreas und das Teams lernen eine ganz neue Seite Südafrikas kennen. Inzwischen haben sie schon mehr als 2000 Kilometer Strecke hinter sich gebracht.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Einer der symbolträchtigsten Lebensräume der iberischen Halbinsel ist der Mittelmeerwald, das Land des Iberischen Luchses, einer einzigartigen und faszinierenden Raubkatze mit einer Erfolgsgeschichte bei der Erhaltung der Tiere. Korkeichen und Steineichen sind die Herren dieser herrlichen Wälder. Und diese Wälder beherbergen eine einzigartige und endemische Fauna. Damit ist diese Region einer der wichtigsten Biodiversitäts-Hotspots der Erde.

programme.title: Die letzten Kamelkarawanen der Sahara
programme.desc: Die letzten Kamelkarawanen der Sahara? Ein Film von Monika Hielscher & Matthias HeederBereits zu Zeiten der Pharaonen zogen sie durch die Sandwüste zwischen dem heutigen Sudan und Ägypten: Kamel-Karawanen, beladen mit Elfenbein, Salz, Straußenfedern und anderen Kostbarkeiten. Bis heute folgen die Beduinenstämme in der Sahara diesen uralten Handelsrouten, nur sind inzwischen die Kamele selbst die Ware, die nach Ägypten verkauft wird. Einer der wichtigsten und gleichzeitig gefährlichsten Pfade führt von Kordufan und Darfur nach Süd-Ägypten. Es ist der Darb al-Arbain - Der Weg der 40 Tage?. Nur erfahrene Karawanenführer trauen sich diesen Marsch zu. Planet Weltweit hat sich mit auf die strapaziöse Reise durch wüstenhafte Hitze und Trockenheit begeben.

programme.title: Die Holzfäller von British Columbia
programme.desc: Lange galt British Columbia als El Dorado der Holzfäller. Schneise um Schneise schlugen sie in den Urwald, holten die edlen Hölzer heraus, um damit die Bauwirtschaft oder die Papierindustrie zu beliefern. Die einseitige Ausrichtung der Wirtschaft auf die Ausbeutung der Wälder bereitet jedoch gewaltige Probleme, und das nicht erst seit der Wirtschaftskrise. Neue Lösungen müssen gefunden werden, um die Waldwirtschaft und die einmaligen Wälder zu erhalten. Auswirkungen hat dies auch für das Städtchen Revelstoke, in dem der Unternehmer Cal March sein kleines Unternehmen betreibt. Es ist eine der letzten verbliebenen Holzfirmen in der Gegend. Wir habenCal March besucht und mit ihm die Veränderungen erlebt, mit denen die moderne Holzwirtschaft die Zukunft meistern will.

programme.title: Die Meerfrauen von Japan
programme.desc: "Ama" nennen sie sich, Frauen des Meeres. Bis ins hohe Alter holen sie kostbare Meeresfrüchte vom Grund des Ozeans, trotzen der Tiefe nur mit der Kraft ihres Atems. Ihre Haut ist von Wind und Wasser gegerbt, ihre Stimme tief und laut. Seit Jahrzehnten teilen sich neun Frauen von der japanischen Halbinsel Shima ihr Schicksal auf einem Boot und sind dabei zu einer eigenen engen Meeres-Familie zusammengewachsen. Kazu Yamamoto ist mit ihren knapp 80 Jahren die Älteste der Gruppe, eine Ama in fünfter Generation. Ans Aufhören denkt sie längst noch nicht: "Im Meer kann ich meinen Körper besser fühlen und bewegen als an Land. Einmal im Wasser, verschwinden alle Schmerzen, auch der Rücken tut mir plötzlich nicht mehr weh", erzählt Kazu Yamamoto. Planet Weltweit taucht in die geschlossene Welt einer Gruppe von Ama ein.

programme.title: New York
programme.desc: New York - Sehnsuchtsort für Menschen aus der ganzen Welt. Wer es hier schafft, schafft es überall. Das dachte auch junge italienische Fleischersohn Tony Amato, als er in den 1940er Jahren hierher kam, um sich den Traum vom eigenen Opernhaus zu verwirklichen. Zusammen mit seiner Frau Sally kaufte er ein heruntergekommenes Haus in der Bowery Street, einer damals berüchtigten Straße in Lower Manhattan. Das Haus, drei Stockwerke hoch und drei Fenster breit, bekam eine Bühne, einen Orchestergraben, einen Kostümfundus, Werkstätten und Lagerräume für die Bühnendekorationen. Der Saal wirkt kaum größer als ein Wohnzimmer - seine 107 Plätze sind immer ausverkauft. Noch immer ist Tony Amato Dreh- und Angelpunkt dieser Miniaturoper - selbst nur knapp 1,50 groß, in Turnschuhen. Hosenträger halten den kleinen drahtigen Mann, so scheint es. Die Stimme ist fest, die Augen strahlen. Er dirigiert, singt, springt, lacht, schimpft. Maestro Tony Amato ist 88 Jahre alt. Er steckt mitten in den Proben zu Cos? fan tutte?, der letzten Produktion der Saison. Planet Weltweit wirft einen Blick hinter die Bühne des kleinsten Opernhauses der Welt mitten in New York.Feierabendverkehr in Manhattan. Am Steuer seines Wagens sitzt der Tenor Vincent Titone und singt sich warm. Er ist auf dem Weg in d ...

programme.title: Wo Japans grüner Tee wächst
programme.desc: Kyuchu - Wo Japans grüner Tee wächstEin Film von Ilka Franzmann Grüner Tee ist in Japan viel mehr als ein Getränk. Er ist der Schlüssel zur japanischen Kultur - Genuss, Philosophie und Lebenskunst in einem. Grünen Tee zu trinken, gilt in Japan als Kunst. Im Frühjahr wartet ganz Japan auf den First Flush - die erste Ernte des edlen Sencha-Tees von der Insel Kyushu. Hier liegt das größte Bioteeanbaugebiet des Landes. Planet Weltweit begleitet den Herstellungsprozess von Japans legendärem Grüntee, forscht nach dem Geheimnis seiner heilenden Kräfte und zeigt auch, wie tief das Getränk inzwischen Japans Gesellschaft durchdrungen hat.Der 60-jährige Kazuo Watanabe hat sein Leben dem grünen Tee gewidmet, wie sein Vater, sein Großvater, seine ganze Familie. Der Biofarmer ist Teebauer und hat seit Jahren einen großen Traum - er will den besten Tee Japans produzieren. Wie nah er seinem Ideal kommt, zeigt sich auch dieses Jahr erst wieder bei der Ernte. Zehn Tage dauert es vom Beginn des Pflückens bis zur trinkfertigen Teeportion. Der Farmer setzt auf behutsame Herstellungsmethoden ohne Pestizide. Seine Plantagen liegen inmitten der imposanten Vulkanlandschaft auf der Insel Kyushu. Der nährstoffreiche Boden, das saubere Quellwasser und das subtropische Klima schaffen ideale Voraussetzung ...

programme.title: Der Whisky-Mythos von Islay
programme.desc: Die schottische Insel Islay ist Heimat von acht traditionellen Whisky-Brennereien, die unter Kennern einen ausgezeichneten Ruf genießen. Das Wasser, der Torf und das Jod des Meeres sind die besonderen Elemente des Whiskys, der die Insel berühmt gemacht hat. Doch nicht nur das: Die Herstellung des berühmten Getränks sorgt für Arbeitsplätze auf Islay, ist Stolz und zugleich Lebensgrundlage ihrer charismatischen Bewohner. Planet Weltweit hat die Insel besucht und erlebt, wie das schottische Nationalgetränk Leben und Arbeit der Menschen auf Islay bestimmt.

programme.title: Marokkos weißes Gold
programme.desc: Die Arganie, ein dornenbewehrter Baum, wächst nur im Südwesten Marokkos. Seine Früchte liefern das begehrte Arganöl, welches von den Frauen der Region seit Jahrhunderten in mühevoller Handarbeit produziert wird. Inzwischen kommen auch Europäer auf den Geschmack dieser einzigartigen Kostbarkeit. Und nicht nur das: Neben seinen kulinarischen Qualitäten lässt sich das Öl ebenso gut als Kosmetikprodukt und Heilmittel vermarkten. Planet Weltweit hat den Frauen Marokkos bei der aufwändigen Ölherstellung über die Schulter geschaut und beobachtet, wie sie sie versuchen, ihr traditionelles Kleinod für den internationalen Wettbewerb vorzubereiten.Sechs Uhr morgens in einem kleinen Dorf im Südwesten Marokkos. Die Männer sind bereits zur Arbeit aufgebrochen. Auch Arbia el Kasri verlässt das Haus, um ihrem Beruf nachzugehen. Vor fünf Jahren noch war es für eine Frau unvorstellbar außerhalb des Hauses Arbeit zu finden. In dieser Region Marokkos verlassen die Bäuerinnen eigentlich nie ihre Douar, ihre kleinen Dörfer. Doch nun sind es einige Hunderte, die sich wie Arbia täglich in kleinen Kooperativen einfinden, welche die Frauen selbst gegründet haben. Hier produzieren sie Arganöl - eine Kunst, die Marokkanerinnen bereits seit Jahrhunderten beherrschen. Das Öl ist überaus nährstoffre ...

programme.title: Der Weinpriester von Bali
programme.desc: Bali - Tropenparadies und Insel der Götter. Dem 42-jährigen Hindu Rai Budarsa gelang es als Erstem, Wein auf Bali zu kultivieren. Dreimal im Jahr kann auf der tropischen Insel geerntet werden. Für den Unternehmer ein Segen - doch für den gläubigen Hindu in Anbetracht der vielen religiösen Feste und Zeremonien eine Herausforderung. Ob Rai Budarsa der Balanceakt zwischen dem harten Alltag eines Unternehmers und seinen religiösen Verpflichtungen gelingt, davon erzählt diese Episode von Planet Weltweit.Bereits seit einer Stunde wartet die Prozession für die Leichenbestattung auf der Straße. Rai Budarsa streift eilig sein Poloshirt und die Bermudas ab, denn als höchster Vertreter einer Priesterkaste muss er jede Zeremonie in seiner Gemeinde leiten. Als sein Blackberry klingelt, schafft er es gerade noch den Knoten seines schwarzen Sarongs festzuziehen, bevor er den Anruf entgegennimmt. Es ist sein Kellermeister, der Australier Don Buchanan: Ihm fehlen Flaschen für die Abfüllung des Pino de Bali, dem Spitzenprodukt seines Unternehmens Hatten Wines. Der Container mit den Flaschen hängt irgendwo fest - ausgerechnet jetzt, wo während der religiösen Feiertage auf Bali die Restaurants und Hotels mit dem regionalen Wein beliefert werden müssen. Im Laufschritt verspricht Rai Budar ...

programme.title: Gilberto Gil
programme.desc: Brazilian artist Gilberto Gil returns to Jazz à Vienne in France with a new round of singing that is inspired by his latest album ‘Fé na Festa': a mixture of celebration, tradition and even some rock now and then. Gilberto Gil, worldwide known for as musician and the Brazilian minister of Culture, was one of the pioneers of the cultural movement ‘tropicalismo'. This movement, with a strong character of social protest, combines elements of traditional Brazilian culture with modern art forms. Gilberto Gil's new sound clearly has its roots in Brazilian culture, yet it is always inspired by jazz.

programme.title: Art Blakey
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Omar Sosa, Childo Tomas, Ernesto Simpson & Leandro Saint-Hill
programme.desc: While always keeping one foot firmly anchored in the traditions of his home country, Cuba, Omar Sosa tirelessly explores music from the Caribbean to India, and West Africa to the Arab world. Since he left Cuba in 1993, the pianist has been blending his Afro-Cuban roots with jazz, hip hop, electro and world music. For his 2018 performance at Théâtre de Villefranche-sur-Saône, he brings to stage his Quarteto Afrocubano members Childo Tomas (electric bass & vocals), Ernesto Simpson (drums), and Leandro Saint-Hill (saxophones, flute, percussion & vocals). Together, they create a riveting instrumental dialogue. Celebrating rhythm in all its forms, this Omar Sosa concert is an intense and mystical experience.

programme.title: Bootsy Collins
programme.sub-title: Casper the Funky Ghost: Bootsy Collins à Vienne
programme.desc: Bootsy Collins, famed for playing with George Clinton and his very own Rubber Band, is used to playing syncopated, hard and relentlessly rhythmic music. With this unique style Bootsy was a major influence on the development of funk. Now in his 60s, the bassist seems animated by a new energy that reflects his new work on the album ‘Tha Funk Capitol of the World'. With this album, Bootsy Collins pays tribute to the artists with whom he worked during his frantic career: from James Brown and Parliament-Funkadelic to Fatboy Slim. During this concert, recorded at the festival Jazz à Vienne, Bootsy maintains that same energy, giving a spectacular show.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, The Walk
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Tony Bennett
programme.desc: Relive the magic of one of the most beloved crooners in music history in his prime: Tony Bennett! Recorded live in London's Royal Albert Hall on March 2, 1974, this enchanting performance showcases Bennett's remarkable vocal prowess and charisma to full effect. Bennett is accompanied by his musical director Torrie Zito and an orchestra of British musicians that includes Kenny Clare (drums), Don Lusher (trombone), and Kenny Baker (trumpet). Tune in for Bennett's captivating take on songs “The Good Things in Life”, “My Favorite Things”, “My Love”, “I've Got Five Dollars”, “It Don't Mean a Thing”, and “Maybe This Time” in this magical concert recording.

programme.title: Charles Bradley, William Aukstik, Frederick Deboe & Michael Deller
programme.sub-title: Charles Bradley: The Screaming Eagle Of Soul
programme.desc: This concert of soul singer Charles Bradley (1948-2017) was recorded in an intimate setting in Paris in September 2014. Before considering a career in music, Bradley had long tried to make ends meet with a series of small jobs. It was only in 1996 that he finally followed in the footsteps of his idol and soul icon James Brown, with whom he shared an exceptional ability to bring audiences to ecstasy. Bradley has developed a unique sound that combines funk, soul, and R&B, but still tinged with Brown influences.

programme.title: David Guetta
programme.desc: David Guetta's story is told chronologically through his major hit singles. We chart his career from the earliest performances to the time he was signed to a major label and his breakthrough single was released all the way through to today. New interviews with emerging pop acts, music journalists and record producers to add insight into the life of David Guetta.

programme.title: Diana Ross & The Supremes
programme.desc: Diana Ross & Supremes- America's most successful female vocal group of all time was formed by four Detroit schoolgirls in the late 50s. Diana Ross (26 March 1944, Detroit, Michigan, USA), Betty McGlown (b. 1943, Detroit, Michigan, USA), Florence Ballard (b. 30 June 1943, Rosetta, Mississippi, USA, d. 22 February 1976, Detroit, Michigan, USA) and Mary Wilson (b. 6 March 1944, Greenville, Mississippi, USA) named themselves the Primettes in tribute to the local male group, the Primes - who themselves found fame in the 60s as the Temptations.

programme.title: Lenny Kravitz
programme.desc: American singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer, actor and arranger, whose "retro" style incorporates elements of rock, blues, soul, R&B, funk, jazz, reggae, hard rock, psychedelic, pop, folk and ballads. In addition to singing lead and backing vocals, Kravitz often plays all the guitar, bass, drums, keyboards, and percussion himself when recording. He won the Grammy Award for Best Male Rock Vocal Performance four years in a row from 1999 to 2002, breaking the record for most wins in that category as well as setting the record for most consecutive wins in one category by a male.

programme.title: Adrien Perruchon, Symfonieorkest Vlaanderen & Josef Špaček
programme.sub-title: Works by Ravel, Lalo, Ginastera a. o.
programme.desc: French conductor Adrien Perruchon and the Flanders Symphony Orchestra take us on a musical journey to Argentine, Spain, and Mexico, in this March 1, 2017 concert performance at Concertgebouw Brugge in Belgium. The program opens with Édouard Lalo's Spanish Symphony for violin and orchestra, Op. 21, featuring Czech violinist Josef Špaček as the soloist. This is followed by Mathias Coppens' Music for Orchestra, Op. 12. The program continues with Alberto Ginastera's Dances from Estancia, Op. 8a, and Aaron Copland's El Salón México. Also on the program is Maurice Ravel's famous Boléro. The program comes to a close with Arturo Márquez's Danzón No. 2.

programme.title: Evgeny Kissin, Nikolai Demidenko, Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra & Antoni Wit
programme.desc: Antoni Wit conducts the Warsaw Philharmonic Orchestra in performances of Chopin's Piano Concertos No. 1, Op. 11 and No. 2, Op. 21. Soloists are Nikolai Demidenko and Evgeny Kissin. After performing the first concerto, Demidenko encores with Chopin's Mazurka Op. 17/4. Kissin closes the concert with Chopin's Etude Op. 10/12 and the Waltz in E minor, Op. post. This concert was part of the celebration of Chopin's 200th anniversary in 2010. Chopin composed the second concerto one year before the Concerto No. 1 and completed both works at the age of 20, before leaving his home country Poland and moving to Paris.

programme.title: Les Dissonances & David Grimal
programme.sub-title: Brahms - Symphony No. 1 in C minor, Op. 68
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances present Johannes Brahms's Symphony No. 1 in C minor, Op. 68. Brahms realized he was expected to compose a symphony that would match the musical standards established by Ludwig van Beethoven. After working on it for at least fourteen years, he completed his Symphony No. 1 in 1876. Brahms's symphony was hailed as ‘Beethoven's Tenth': a worthy successor to Beethoven's Symphony No. 9. Brahms's work contains several references to Beethoven. For instance, the main theme of the fourth movement – first appearing in the strings – resembles the ‘Ode to Joy' in the finale of Beethoven's Symphony No. 9. This performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris, France, in 2014.

programme.title: Mikhail Pletnev, Russian National Orchestra & Lucas Debargue
programme.sub-title: Pletnev conducts Bizet & Ravel's Concerto No. 1
programme.desc: Mikhail Pletnev leads the Russian National Orchestra (RNO) in a performance of Maurice Ravel's Piano Concerto No. 1 with Lucas Debargue as the soloist. The concert opens with a selection of music by Georges Bizet based on Alphonse Daudet's play 'L'Arlésienne'. The music is compiled by Mikhail Pletnev. The first movement of Ravel's Piano Concerto No. 1 contains five distinctive themes, of which three are reminiscent of jazz. Debargue's performance of Ravel's concerto is followed by Gabriel Fauré's Barcarolle No. 4. The performance was recorded at Tchaikovsky Concert Hall in Moscow as part of the Ninth RNO Grand Festival.

programme.title: Philippe Jordan, Orchestre de l'Opéra national de Paris, Choeur de l'Opéra national de Paris & Ricarda Merbeth
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphony No. 9 in D minor, Op. 125
programme.desc: Swiss conductor Philippe Jordan and the Orchestre de l'Opéra national de Paris recorded all of Ludwig van Beethoven's symphonies in 2014-2015. In this program, maestro Jordan presents Beethoven's final symphony: Symphony No. 9 in D minor, Op. 125. He conducts the Orchestre and Choeurs de l'Opéra national de Paris and four vocal soloists Ricarda Merbeth (soprano), Daniela Sindram (mezzosoprano), Robert Dean Smith (tenor), and Günther Groissböck (bass). Beethoven composed his last Symphony when his hearing had all but gone, between 1822 and 1824. Symphony No. 9 is the longest and most ambitious of Beethoven's symphonies. Most striking is the piece's finale movement, which includes a choir and four vocal soloists singing a setting of Friedrich Schiller's poem ‘An die Freude' (Ode to Joy). This performance was recorded at Opéra Bastille in Paris, France, in 2015.

programme.title: Rainbow Reef Relaxation 1
programme.desc: Sit back, relax and enjoy the dazzling world of coral reefs in 4K you embark on a journey through some of the most vibrant underwater reefs on our blue planet - including many scenes which no longer look like this due to coral bleaching. From the cinematographer: "The footage for this film was shot over a period of some years in French Polynesia, Micronesia, Indonesia and East Timor. Unfortunately there are not that vibrant anymore today. Coral reefs have suffered from the rise of water temperature, rise in acidity, destructive fishing methods and severe storms caused by climate change." - Peter Schneider. "Rainbow Reef Relaxation" is a 3-hour long, sweeping yet majestic & vibrant underwater journey to the world's most beautiful lagoons, as captured by Nature Relaxation collaborator Peter Schneider (Underwatercam) paired with ambient underwater sounds and brand new ambient music by the Cynic Project. Filmed in High Definition several years ago, thanks to its age this film offers magical glimpses of an underwater world that is bursting with life, color, and beauty.

programme.title: Flying Over Iceland
programme.desc: Flying Over Iceland: Part I is a stunning yet soothing aerial journey to the remote fjiords and valleys of eastern Iceland. The first of a series of 1 hour films, Part I begins at sunrise on a perfect summer day in Breiðdalsvík, where a golden sun lights up the majestic valley. After soaring through the golden sea mists and offering a glimpse of the stunning Breiðdalur Valley (its name means ‘Wide Valley'), viewers then head inland to a hidden, magical arched waterfall for a refreshing immersive flight that begins at the base of the falls and reaches above the clouds. Next, as the morning turns into a sunlit afternoon, viewers are swept inland to the crystal clear waters of the the impressive Breiðdalsá river, to cool off in some falls along with a pair of local swans. Well known for salmon fishing, the turquoise blue river winds its way scenically across the valley basin to the sea, which is where the film ends - but not before a chance encounter with a local reindeer! The final flight in Part 1 offers a sunny afternoon look at the tiny village of Breiðdalsvík from afar and offers amazing blue water vistas of with green islands, seagulls, a rock island that that looks like a cat, a scenic lighthouse, and more.

programme.desc: Die Tonka-Makaken bevölkern die Tempel auf Sri Lanka. In einem der Clans erblickt das kleine Affen-Mädchen Gremlin das Licht der Welt. Von Geburt an muss es sich in dem lauten Gewusel aus Familienbanden und Fehden mit benachbarten Truppen behaupten. Das Gruppenleben ist von einer strengen Hierarchie bestimmt. Die Machtkämpfe zwischen und innerhalb der Familienverbände bergen ebenso viele Gefahren wie lauernde Greifvögel und die angrenzende Straße. Allzu oft geraten die noch wehrlosen Babys zwischen die Fronten. Bei Übergriffen durch Ranghöhere müssen Mütter oft zusehen, wie unsanft mit ihrem Nachwuchs umgegangen wird. Nur jedes dritte Makaken-Kind kann sich durchsetzen und überlebt seine ersten Monate. Der niedrige Rang der Mutter und obendrein ihre auffällige weiße Schwanzspitze sind nicht die besten Voraussetzungen für die kleine Gremlin. Doch das aufgeweckte Äffchen lernt schnell dazu und entpuppt sich als wahre Kämpfernatur.
